## Question 7: Write an SQL query on Sales_Transactions to list all duplicate keys and their counts using the business key (Customer_ID + Product_ID + Txn_Date + Txn_Amount).

SQL Query:

SELECT 
    Customer_ID,
    Product_ID,
    Txn_Date,
    Txn_Amount,
    COUNT(*) AS duplicate_count
FROM Sales_Transactions
GROUP BY 
    Customer_ID,
    Product_ID,
    Txn_Date,
    Txn_Amount
HAVING COUNT(*) > 1;

This query groups records by the business key and returns combinations that appear more than once.

Duplicate combination:
(C101, P11, 2025-12-01, 4000) appears 3 times.

