## Question 8: Enforcing Referential Integrity

Customers_Master Table:

| CustomerID | CustomerName | City       |
|------------|-------------|-----------|
| C101 | Rahul Mehta | Mumbai |
| C102 | Anjali Rao  | Bengaluru |
| C103 | Suresh Iyer | Chennai |
| C104 | Neha Singh  | Delhi |

Customer_ID values in Sales_Transactions:
C101, C102, C103, C104, C105, C106

Customer_ID values not present in Customers_Master:
C105, C106

SQL Query to detect violations:

SELECT DISTINCT s.Customer_ID
FROM Sales_Transactions s
LEFT JOIN Customers_Master c
ON s.Customer_ID = c.CustomerID
WHERE c.CustomerID IS NULL;

This query identifies Customer_ID values in Sales_Transactions that do not exist in Customers_Master.

